==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[uncia]]'', 1/12th part.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-inch.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪntʃ|-ɪntʃ]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}
# A unit of [[length]] equal to one-twelfth of a [[foot]] and equivalent to exactly 2.54 [[centimetre]]s.
# (''figurative'') An unspecified but very short distance.
#:''"Don't move an '''inch'''!"''

